         <seg xml:id="ex1082023-02-0311-31-41" type="excerpt" status="reviewed">
        <pb edRef="inst:4434" n="1b"/><lb edRef="inst:4434" n="1b1"/> bsam dang sbyor ba las 'khrungs <abbr>pa'i</abbr> || dpa' bo de dang de'i bka' || nyes 'joMs de sgrub tshogs bcas la ||sgo <abbr>gsum</abbr> dang bas <rs type="person" ana="corpusmd:unnamed_reference" ref="4953">bdag</rs> nyid 'dud ||<!--TODO check if this way of tagging works. This verse is found only in instance id:4434. It is lacking in the blockprint version id:5591 and in the gSung thor bu, id:5592. It may have been authored by the scribe.-->
         </seg><seg xml:id="ex1082023-02-0311-33-11" type="excerpt" status="reviewed"><!--TODO Q check the alternative readings from blockprint; why does it not recognize the end of segment?-->
